      "source": "target",
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A 2018 Toyota Camry with a P0171 code, running lean, is a bit of a tricky situation. Since you've checked the Mass Air Flow (MAF) sensor and it looks fine, let's consider other potential culprits. You might want to check the fuel pressure, as a low fuel pressure can cause the engine to run lean. It's also wise to inspect the fuel injectors for proper operation. If they're clogged or leaking, they might not be delivering the right amount of fuel. Lastly, don't forget to examine the oxygen sensors and the engine control unit (ECU), as they play a crucial role in maintaining the right air-fuel ratio. If the ECU is misinterpreting the data, it could lead to a lean condition. Keep an eye out for any signs of wear or damage in these components. Remember, a lean-running engine can be a bit of a wild beast, so it's always good to approach the issue with caution and thoroughness. Good luck!",
